<br>
&quot;She's here...&quot; then-<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Queen Raven has returned...&quot;, The gaurd stood before the Queen.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yakut nodded, eyes filling with tears of joy. The Shamaness ran out to her eldest daughter, wrapped her in an embrace. She pulled back tears staining her ivory face.<br>
<br>
&quot;My Ravey...your home.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yakut noticed her daughter was some-what wounded but feared not. Raven was the Demi-Goddess of Pride and would heal quickly enough. She wrapped her arm around her child's shoulders and lead her to the main hut. She sat Ravey down in her throne and served her a cup of warm tea before sitting in her own throne.<br>
<br>
The Shamaness Queen stood up and as her Amazons gathered around she spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let it be known, through the entire Nation, Queen Raven of Tanais River Valley has returned. and Home she will stay...&quot;<br>
<br>
She took her staff from it place leaning against her throne, and lifted it into the air.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hail Vasilissa Raven!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Amazons cheer and all scattered back to their daily jobs. Yakut sits down after putting her staff back in its place.<br>
<br>
&quot;Welcome Home.&quot;, she smiled at her daughter. <p>-|-Queen Yakut-|-<br>
-Shamaness of the Old Ways-<br>
&quot;Just as daughter becomes mother, the student becomes the teacher. Their strength will be their unity. Their courage will be their guide.&quot;-Yakut</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonqueenyakut>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/18/02 11:15:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonqueenraven>Amazon Queen Raven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/03 6:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hometown.aol.com/magickalamzn/images/raven1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A daughter's joy...</span><hr size=1> When her mother wrapped her arms around her wounded torso, she brought her weak arms stained with dry blood and dirt.  Tears stung her eyes as they pleaded to come out, but she fought them back.<br>
<br>
She was glad to be back in her mother's arms.<br>
<br>
She softly whispered in a youthful voice, &quot;Mommy...&quot; but Raven pressed her inner child aside, sense to her, she was not important.  <br>
<br>
With a quick clear of her throat, she returned to her normal prideful state.  She gave her mother a soft kiss on the cheak and walked with her into the Queen's hut.  With her first step she engulfed the familiar air, savoring the scent she had missed for so long.<br>
<br>
She sat by the identical, but at a smaller scale, seat to the right of her mother's.  Raven had not felt so rested is such a long time.  She had fallen into a quick day dream from her exhaustion until her mother stood to announce her daughter's return.  Then, Raven's hazel occulars fell back onto her mother.<br>
<br>
A faint smile fell across her lips as her mother spoke to all the Amazons that had gathered.  When they all began to clap she stood and raised a weak hand in a greeting matter.  And when they answered her mother's hail with the same words, a larger smile took over her lips as her pride went soaring.<br>
<br>
Raven took her seat back.  &quot;It's good to be home, Mother.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Quote the Raven...Never More.<br>
<br>
.-~ Queen Raven ~-.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonqueenyakut>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen of Tanis River Valley</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/16/03 5:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hometown.aol.com/amznqyakut1/images/yakut3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well,</span><hr size=1> The Shamaness smiled at her daughter. She stood up and kneeled at Raven's feet and smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;I want you to go to your hut, get some rest. Give your powers time to heal you...When You wake up I'll bring you some chamomille tea and venison.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yakut took her daughter's hand and kissed it before standing up. She leaned over kissing her daughter's forehead before turning on her heals and moving to the back of the room to make up the tea. While, watching the water her fingers played with the blue pentagram around her neck. The Shamaness hummed a little tune while fixing up the tea. <p>-|-Queen Yakut-|-<br>
-Shamaness of the Old Ways-<br>
&quot;Just as daughter becomes mother, the student becomes the teacher. Their strength will be their unity. Their courage will be their guide.&quot;-Yakut</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#6F6F6F>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29>Amazons of the Tanais River Valley</a> <font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href="http://pub163.ezboard.com/bmythicalodysseyforum">Home</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.3m<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

